The paper discusses the design of distributed algorithms for collective decision-making in large groups of robots, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also draws inspiration from biological systems, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability and flexibility of these algorithms, which could be related to the field of swarm intelligence (cs.SI).
